In this letter, President Donald Trump provides a consolidated report on the deployments of the United States Armed Forces equipped for combat, in accordance with the War Powers Resolution. The report focuses on military operations in support of US counterterrorism efforts around the globe, particularly in the US Central and Africa Commands' areas of responsibility. The report highlights ongoing military operations against al-Qa'ida, the Taliban, and associated forces, as well as operations against ISIS in Iraq and Syria. It also mentions deployments in Afghanistan, Yemen, Jordan, Lebanon, Turkey, East Africa, Libya, the Lake Chad Basin and Sahel Region, Cuba, the Philippines, Egypt, and Kosovo. The letter emphasizes the success of these operations in degrading ISIS capabilities, while acknowledging the ongoing armed conflict in Afghanistan and against the Taliban. The report concludes with President Trump's assurance that additional measures will be taken if necessary to protect the US and its interests from terrorist threats.